title: Farm Weighting Adjustments
body:
## We're now getting to the point where the number of projects asking for Syrup Pools/farms or to host IFOs is super high. 

It's so high that just keeping frequent communication between all the various groups is a challenge. 

We will keep adding as many new projects as possible, but we also need to make sure that the farm rewards don't dilute too much.

## How do we do this? 

A very simple solution is to cycle down, or out low-value farms.

Low-value can be equated to any number of the below:

- Low number of holders on BSC
- Low liquidity 
- Low trading volume 

The list goes on, but you get the gist.

To kick this off, our initial proposed changes are as below: 

| LP           | Current Multiplier    | New Multiplier  |
|--------------|-----------------------|-----------------|
| LTC-BNB      |           2           |       0.5       |
| CTK-WBNB     |           1           |       0.5       |
| FIL-WBNB     |           1           |       0.5       |
| ATOM-WBNB    |           1           |       0.5       |
| EOS-WBNB     |           1           |       0.5       |
| bRooBEE-CAKE |          0.2          |       0.1       |
|              | Rewards back to farms |       2.6       |

If this change is approved then cut rewards will flow back into the existing farms which boost rewards ever-so-slightly until new farms are added.
